title: No. 2 Bulldogs Want to Earn Ranking
text:
No. 2 Bulldogs Want to Earn Ranking 
By Norman Seawright III October 3, 2015 Updated Oct 3, 2015 at 7:57 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) -- The University of Minnesota-Duluth (UMD) men's hockey team was ranked second by U.S. College Hockey Online (USCHO) in a preseason pollâ€”and the Bulldogs intend to be worthy of that spot. 
UMD will play an exhibition with Lakehead on October 4, then opens the season with Bemidji State on October 9. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
"We haven't don't anything yet," said Bulldogs senior captain Andy Welinski. "We haven't even stepped on the ice for an exhibition game. I think that message is important that we need to go earn that spot that the preseason poll has given us. Nothing is going to be handed to us early." 
It won't be easy, especially having lost strong players to graduation, but the team may still have what it needs to have a successful season. 
"We lost some key guys, some character and leadership," said head coach Scott Sandelin. "We replaced them with some freshman that I think can help out in the long run, and we also have some guys here that have been here that we expect to kind of step up."
